ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Unique identifier of cells
A short name for the protocol
A unique ID for the protocol
The protocols.io digital object identifier (doi) for the protocol (if applicable)
A general description (100 words or fewer) of the protocol.
Reference publication for the protocol (if applicable).
Culture media used to induce a specific differentiation response. For example ''RPMI 1640 (plus) B27'', ''Neurobasal Media'' or ''StemPro-34 Serum-Free Medium''.
Method applied to cell culture to induce a specific differentiation response. For example ''Embryoid Body'', ''Monolayer'' or ''Inductive Co-Culture''.
Number of days in culture
Small molecules added to stem cell medium to induce a specific differentiation response. For example ''Retinoic Acid'', ''CHIR99021 (GSK-inhibitor)'', ''Activin A'' or ''BMP4''.
Percent of target cells obtained after directed differentiation of origin cell. For example ''95''.
Targeted pathway for specific differentiation response. For example ''Wnt pathway'' or ''Hedgehog signaling pathway''.
Method used to validate origin cell successfully differentiated to target cell. For example ''Pancreatic Cell DTZ Detection Assay'', ''qPCR'', ''Flow Cytometry'' or ''Immunocytochemistry Staining''.
Result confirming successful differentiation to target cell type. For example ''CD103 Positive'', ''Nestin Positive'', ''HCN4 Positive'' or ''CD11C Negative''.
A list of purchased reagents used in the differentiation protocol.
The catalog number of the kit/reagent.
The date of expiration for the kit/reagent, in MM/DD/YYYY format
Appropriate titer and volume recommendations found in kit/reagent Certificate of Analysis. For example ''3.0x10^7''.
The batch or lot number of the kit/reagent. For example ''10001A''.
The manufacturer of the kit/reagent. For example ''Illumina'' or ''ThermoFisher Scientific''.
Describe quality control of the culture, including the status, shape, growth rate, and cell death, etc
ID for the Experiment/settings/run
